[FILE:452:descriptions/desc.primary]
AVRDUDE - AVR Downloader Uploader - is a program for downloading and uploading t
he on-chip memories of s AVR microcontrollers. It can program the Flash and EEPR
OM, and where supported by the programming protocol, it can program fuse and loc
k bits. AVRDUDE also supplies a direct instruction mode allowing one to issue an
y programming instruction to the AVR chip regardless of whether AVRDUDE implemen
ts that specific feature of a particular chip.


